item.title: West Sydney Airport metro line expedited
item.description: Construction work on a metro line connecting the Western Sydney Airport at Badgerys Creek to St Marys will begin before year's end.

item.title: PayPal signups tripled amid lockdown
item.description: Signups to PayPal Australia have almost tripled during the COVID-19 pandemic as Australians flock to online shopping, the payments giant says.

item.title: Morrison regrets pain caused by robo-debt
item.description: Prime Minister Scott Morrison has insisted the federal government is making amends for its bungled robo-debt scheme.

item.title: Vicinity outlines virus hit, raises $1.4b
item.description: Shopping malls owner Vicinity Centres has axed its dividend and is raising $1.4 billion through a share sale to manage the impact on its business caused by the coronavirus pandemic.

item.title: Asia stocks resilient as futures bounce
item.description: Asian shares have pushed to three-month highs as progress on opening up economies helped offset jitters over riots in US cities and unease over Washington's power struggle with Beijing.

item.title: China reports 16 new coronavirus cases
item.description: China has reported the highest daily increase in coronavirus cases in nearly three weeks with 16 new infections discovered on May 31, as the number of so-called imported cases jumped in southwestern Sichuan province.

item.title: Rallies as Brazil political crisis deepens
item.description: Brazilian President Jair Bolsonaro has joined a rally on horseback as supporters urged the closing of the Supreme Court for investigating the right-wing leader, as one of its justices compared the risks to Brazil's democracy with Hitler's Germany.

item.title: India expels two Pakistanis for spying
item.description: The Indian government has expelled two officials working at the Pakistan High Commision in New Delhi after they were held for espionage, the foreign ministry said in a statement.

item.title: Queen rides pony in first public outing
item.description: The Queen has been pictured riding in the grounds of Windsor Castle - her first public appearance since the coronavirus lockdown began.

item.title: Quiz whistleblower Herbert Stempel dies
item.description: Herbert Stempel, the contestant on NBC's Twenty-One who helped uncover the quiz show rigging scandals of the 1950s, has died at the age of 93.
